Note to my fellow commenters; sorry to be a bore, but this isn't really a political issue as it's about interpretations of an existing law, so one's standing on Liberal/Left/Tory/Whatever doesn't really come into it. Neither the DoJ, nor Apple are claiming that anything needs to be changed in any law. It's quite possible that politicians may suggest future changes to laws as a result of this debate, but that is unlikely to be applied in retrospect to this case since it would violate principles of legal predictability.



